.TH "of_dma_match_channel" 9 "of_dma_match_channel" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
of_dma_match_channel \- Check if a DMA specifier matches name
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" of_dma_match_channel
.BI "(struct device_node *np "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ","
.BI "int index "  ","
.BI "struct of_phandle_args *dma_spec "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "np" 12
device node to look for DMA channels
.IP "name" 12
channel name to be matched
.IP "index" 12
index of DMA specifier in list of DMA specifiers
.IP "dma_spec" 12
pointer to DMA specifier as found in the device tree
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Check if the DMA specifier pointed to by the index in a list of DMA
specifiers, matches the name provided. Returns 0 if the name matches and
a valid pointer to the DMA specifier is found. Otherwise returns -ENODEV.
